definition: Lake Superior, one of the Great Lakes 五大湖[Wu3 da4 hu2]
surname Su/abbr. for Soviet Union 蘇維埃|苏维埃 or 蘇聯|苏联/abbr. for Jiangsu province 江蘇|江苏/abbr. for Suzhou city 蘇州|苏州

sentences.english: Ice situation expected to change in Lake Superior.
sentences.chinese: 冰况在苏必利尔湖将会改变。

sentences.english: I came down along Lake Superior ; I'll go back through the Black Hills.
sentences.chinese: 我是沿苏必利尔湖开车来的，准备穿过黑山陵回去。

sentences.english: Seen from the shores of Lake Superior, an August 4 aurora glows green topped with blueish-purple.
sentences.chinese: 8月4日苏必利尔湖上的下绿上紫的极光。

sentences.english: A fat, thick-bodied variety of the lake trout, found in the upper part of Lake Superior.
sentences.chinese: 大湖鳟鱼的一个变种，体肥而厚，分布在苏必利尔湖。

sentences.english: Yeah, I lived on Lake Superior.
sentences.chinese: 是的，我住在苏必利尔湖边。

sentences.english: Long ago, the Chippewa (1) tribe lived on the shores of Lake Superior.
sentences.chinese: 很久以前，奥吉布瓦部落居住在苏必利尔湖岸边。
